  "texts": [
    "However, it also can widen economic inequalities between those who possess the skills and resources to leverage AI and those who lack them.",
    "This divide is gaining recognition as the \"AI Divide\" (Kitsara, 2022).",
    "In response, there is a growing discourse around the \"Democratization of AI\" as a possible solution, which broadly calls for greater participation in the utilization, profitability, development, and governance of AI by all sections of society (Seger et al., 2023)).",
    "In the book \"AI for Everyone?",
    ": Critical Perspectives\", Verdegem (2021) argues that for AI to transform society positively, a \"radical democratization of AI\" is essential, and this can be achieved by adhering to three fundamental principles:• AI should be accessible to everyone."
